Several people accused of corruption at Eskom appeared at the Johannesburg Regional Court on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - Several people accused of corruption at Eskom have been granted bail. Two are former senior managers at the utility. They appeared at the Johannesburg Regional Court on Thursday. READ: Former Eskom managers arrested They were arrested on Thursday morning for allegations relating to contracts for the Kusile power station. This follows investigations pointing to manipulation of contractual agreements between contractors, Eskom employees, and third parties.